North Korea says it will not unilaterally disarm if there is no confidence
North Korea's foreign minister told the United Nations on Saturday that continued sanctions would heighten its mistrust of the United States and that the country would not unilaterally abandon its nuclear weapons under such conditions.
Ri Yong Ho told the World Organization’s General Assembly that North Korea had shown “significant benevolence” within the past year, for example, by stopping nuclear and missile tests, winding down an area for nuclear testing, and vowing not to further develop nuclear weapons and nuclear technology.
"We have not seen a similar reaction from the United States," he said.
